-- Life insurers up on government aid report
-- 
-- Wed Apr 8, 2009 7:35am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/04/08/us-markets-stocks-beforethebell-insurers-idUSTRE5372HH20090408

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of U.S. life insurance companies rose in premarket trade on Wednesday, after the Wall Street Journal reported that the Treasury would extend TARP money to life insurance firms. 

 The deal is expected to be announced in the next several days, the Journal wrote. Hartford Financial surged 24.3 percent to $10.50, Prudential Financial added 9.7 percent to $24.25, MetLife advanced 6.4 percent to $25.70 and Lincoln National was up 13.2 percent to $7.80. (Reporting by  Ryan Vlastelica , Editing by Walker Simon)